
[1]facetious

   FACE'TIOUS, a. [L. facetus; facetia, or plu.]

   1. Merry; sportive; jocular; sprightly with wit and good humor; as a
   facetious companion.

   2. Witty; full of pleasantry playful; exciting laughter; as a facetious
   story; a facetious reply.
